comments.body:
 [~wesmckinn] that would work but the type needs to fully specify the physical layout. If the unit is used to infer the value bit width (32 or 64 bits) then we can't change in the future. So the type would be something like this?
{noformat}
table Time {
  unit: TimeUnit;
  bitWidth: int; // restricted to 32 for sec and millis, and 64 for micros and nanos in v1
}
{noformat}
Possibly we can further limit to millis and nanos only in v1 since they are respectively the most precise for each bitWIdth (millis: 32bits, nanos: 64 bits)
This is a little verbose but explicit and future proof.
